STATE of North Carolina
v.
Pete MUHAMMAD No. 81P18 Supreme Court of North Carolina. April 5, 2018 Pete Muhammad, for Muhammad, Pete. Daniel P. O'Brien, Special Deputy Attorney General, N. Lorrin Freeman, District Attorney, for State of North Carolina.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed by Defendant on the 14th of March 2018 in this matter for a writ of certiorari to review the order of the North Carolina Court of Appeals, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the North Carolina Court of Appeals:

"Dismissed by order of the Court in conference, this the 5th of April 2018."

The following order has been entered on the motion filed on the 14th of March 2018 by Defendant to Proceed In Forma Pauperis:

"Motion Allowed by order of the Court in conference, this the 5th of April 2018."
